(849, 'EH1', 'EDINBURGH', 'Mostly consists of Edinburgh''s Old Town. Also hosts the old GPO building (at EH1 1AA) and the areas immediately to the north of this are also included, that is St. James Centre and the areas down Leith Street and Broughton Street.', ''),
(850, 'EH2', 'EDINBURGH', 'The New Town and central commercial area of Edinburgh which includes Princes Street.', ''),
(851, 'EH3', 'EDINBURGH', 'An odd shaped area surrounding EH1 and EH2 to the north, west and south. It can be divided into three distinct areas:', ''),
(856, 'EH4', 'EDINBURGH', 'Radiates from the older and more central areas out to the suburban areas added to them, as the city grew outwards during the 20th century. EH4, then, branches out from Dean Village and Comely Bank along a corridor centred on the A90 as far as Barnton and Cramond. Central to this area is the Sainsbury''s in Craigleith Retail Park adjacent to the A90.', ''),
(857, 'EH5', 'EDINBURGH', 'Based on a village formerly separate from the city', ' in this case, Granton on the Firth of For'),
(858, 'EH6', 'EDINBURGH', 'Covers Leith, as well as Newhaven bordering it on the west.', ''),
(859, 'EH7', 'EDINBURGH', 'The inner city area between central Edinburgh and Leith, and radiates out to Restalrig and Craigentinny.', ''),
(860, 'EH8', 'EDINBURGH', 'The inner city Southside, Newington and Canongate areas, in the west of the postcode area. It spreads eastwards around Holyrood Park to take in areas like Northfield and Mountcastle', ' being in east Edinburgh these areas have '),
(861, 'EH9', 'EDINBURGH', 'The inner city, Marchmont and Grange, Blackford and around Minto Street, including Causewayside.', ''),
(862, 'EH10', 'EDINBURGH', 'A corridor along the A702 from Bruntsfield, through Morningside as far as Fairmilehead.', ''),
(863, 'EH11', 'EDINBURGH', 'A corridor (rather thin in shape) along the A71 from Haymarket Station, through Gorgie and Stenhouse to Sighthill.', ''),
(864, 'EH12', 'EDINBURGH', 'A corridor along the A8 from Haymarket through Murrayfield and Corstorphine as far as the Gyle.', ''),
(865, 'EH13', 'EDINBURGH', 'Based on the previously separate village of Colinton, and including Oxgangs.', ''),
(866, 'EH14', 'BALERNO, CURRIE, EDINBURGH, JUNIPER GREEN', 'A corridor in south-west Edinburgh starting at Slateford, through Longstone, Wester Hailes, Juniper Green, Currie and on to Balerno.', ''),
(867, 'EH15', 'EDINBURGH', 'Based on Portobello and Duddingston, formerly separate settlements to Edinburgh.', ''),
(868, 'EH16', 'EDINBURGH', 'Based on the formerly separate village of Liberton. It extends north and north-east to Cameron Toll, Craigmillar and Niddrie.', ''),
(869, 'EH17', 'EDINBURGH', 'Based on the formerly separate village of Gilmerton, taking in Moredun and extending westwards as far as Mortonhall.', ''),
